ZH: 我们应该相信司法系统的公正性。
EN: We should believe in the fairness of the judicial system.

ZH: 只有在公正的环境中才能建立长期合作。
EN: Long-term collaboration can only be established in a fair environment.

ZH: 公正的裁决将有助于解决争议。
EN: Fair judgments will help resolve disputes.

ZH: 他的公正使他成为了人们信赖的领导者。
EN: His fairness made him a trusted leader.

ZH: 公正的分配资源是社会稳定的基础。
EN: Fair distribution of resources is the foundation of social stability.

ZH: 每个人都应该享有受公正对待的权利。
EN: Everyone should have the right to be treated fairly.

ZH: 法官应该保持公正，不受外部影响。
EN: Judges should maintain fairness and be free from external influence.

ZH: 只有经过公正的选举才能产生真正的领导者。
EN: Only through fair elections can genuine leaders emerge.

ZH: 公正的竞争有助于促进创新和进步。
EN: Fair competition helps promote innovation and progress.

ZH: 每个人都应该为自己的行为负责，并接受公正的惩罚。
EN: Everyone should be held accountable for their actions and receive fair punishment.

ZH: 公正的审查将帮助提高组织的效率。
EN: Fair reviews will help improve the efficiency of organizations.

ZH: 在公正的基础上建立信任是非常重要的。
EN: Building trust on the basis of fairness is crucial.

ZH: 他的决定是根据公正的原则做出的。
EN: His decision was made based on principles of fairness.

ZH: 我们应该为实现公正社会而努力工作。
EN: We should work hard to achieve a fair society.

ZH: 整个社会应该为保护公正奋斗。
EN: The whole society should strive to protect fairness.

ZH: 公正的调解将有助于解决纠纷。
EN: Fair mediation will help resolve disputes.

ZH: 没有公正，就没有社会公平。
EN: Without fairness, there is no social justice.

ZH: 我们应该努力捍卫公正的法律原则。
EN: We should strive to uphold the principles of fair laws.

ZH: 只有公正的法律才能保护每个人的权利。
EN: Only fair laws can protect the rights of everyone.

ZH: 公正是建立和谐社会的基石。
EN: Fairness is the cornerstone of building a harmonious society.
